u}(x) = \sum_{k=0}^{\infty}  rac{(-1)^k}{k! \Gamma(
u+k+1)} \left( rac{x}{2}ight)^{
u+2k}. For an integer index 
u = -n (n > 0), we have J_{-n}(x) = \sum_{k=0}^{\infty}  rac{(-1)^k}{k! (k-n)!} \left( rac{x}{2}ight)^{2k-n}. The terms with k < n vanish because the factorial of a negative integer is defined as infinity. Setting k = n + m, we get: J_{-n}(x) = \sum_{m=0}^{\infty}  rac{(-1)^{n+m}}{(n+m)! m!} \left( rac{x}{2}ight)^{2(n+m)-n} = \sum_{m=0}^{\infty}  rac{(-1)^n (-1)^m}{m! (n+m)!} \left( rac{x}{2}ight)^{n+2m} = (-1)^n \sum_{m=0}^{\infty}  rac{(-1)^m}{m! (n+m)!} \left( rac{x}{2}ight)^{n+2m} = (-1)^n J_n(x).
